transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling customer service. I can help you.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I just have a question. If I order the Viagra, does that automatically put me on automatic shipments?

Speaker 1: Let me pull up your account so I can see what kind of account you have. What's your name and birthday?

Speaker 2: It's Dave Gutschus, G-U-C-H-E-S, 10-18-44.

Speaker 1: Okay, so if you do it over the phone, you don't have to be on an automatic.

Speaker 2: Okay, but if I do it on the computer, it's automatic?

Speaker 1: If you don't uncheck the box, it could possibly be automatic, yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, well then I need to, I don't have my wallet with me, so I need to change the credit card. So if I call again and order, it's not—and I know I'm repeating myself—but I don't want to get caught up in automatic shipments, if you know what I mean.

Speaker 1: Okay, thanks for your patience with me. Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: You're welcome, bye-bye.
